        </level>
        <paragraph>
          <num>323.</num>
          <content>
            <p>We assume that additional ongoing costs for new companies over the appraisal period will be negligible. New companies are more likely to digitally file. This is supported by the Companies House report which found that companies older than 10 years are more likely to file by paper.<authorialNote marker="109"><p> <a href="https://www.bi.team/publications/increasing-uptake-of-digital-services-at-companies-house/"><u>https://www.bi.team/publications/increasing-uptake-of-digital-services-at-companies-house/</u></a><u> </u></p></authorialNote> Also, the research identified that the strongest predictor of a company paper filing is whether it paper filed the previous year. This indicates that paper filing is a repeat behaviour.</p>
